  "text": "Gel-shift assays using either the IREu or IREd elements and total proteins extracted from yeast cells grown under the same conditions described above for the lacZ experiments, revealed the formation of two specific DNA-protein complexes (Fig. 7) . Nonspecific competition with 10ϫ and 100ϫ plasmid pUC19 DNA did not reduce the formation of these complexes (data not shown), whereas specific competition showed such a decrease (Fig. 7A, compare lanes 8 and 9 to lane 3, and Fig. 7B,   FIG. 5 . Sequence alignment of the two IRE elements in IME1 to known UAS elements. The sequence of the STRE element is underlined. Given is the sequence used in band-shift assays as a probe for the binding of Msn2/4p [CITATION_1] . The SCB element (3) is in opposite orientation.",
